items.name: Alf - (Dreambooth Trained)
items.description:
High Quality Dreambooth (JP repo) trained model of the 1980s television star, Alf. Created using 20 HQ images from the TV show and promos.

Trigger with "Alf Person"

(yes, put person also). Use "Hi-Res fix" with the settings you'd normally use for best results. Use prompt weighting and/or Controlnet to get maximum flexibility out of this likeness model and to limit clones/doubles from appearing. Trained locally using JP's repo (24gb VRAM req / arguably the best for likenesses).

Why a full checkpoint/2GB model for 1 subject?

Simply because the trained checkpoint gives you the best quality to start w/. LoRAs are fantastic for lots of things, but for human likenesses they don't match up to Dreambooth trained checkpoints.

"I need a LoRA for my workflow!"

It's easy to extract a LoRA from an SD checkpoint on your own if you prefer a LoRA for your workflow. For instance you can use the Auto1111 extension "Supermerger" to extract a LoRA. That said, LoRA will not match the quality of the original Dreambooth model (loss incurred). Note: I've also been uploading updated versions to some of these models after posting the pure checkpoint first. If after extracting to LoRA the generated LoRA holds up well then I will try to add those as alternate versions.

Some samples images were generated w/ Controlnet for initial guidance and thus won't be reproducible exactly with only metadata (don't think Civitai lists whether or not CN was used).

items.name: Maria Becerra [LORA]
items.description:
V2.0

  1. Spanish:

He usado una nueva configuración para que el resultado sea mucho más realista. Trata de usar EpicRealism.

Es posible que el nombre del LORA cambie, así que no lo copies directamente de CIVITAI, mejor selecciónalo del apartado de LORAS de Stable Diffusion para que no haya errores en la generación de imágenes.

Mi configuración usando EpicRealism:

  • Lora Strength: 1

  • Prompt: Explicación simple de la imagen (pruebe primero sin palabras clave adicionales)

    En el caso de esta Lora, el prompt debe comenzar con "A woman...".

  • Prompt negativo: cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2), asian, chinese, (epiCNegative:0.9)

  • Sampling steps: >20 (si la imagen tiene errores o artefactos, use steps más altos)

  • CFG Scale: 5

  • Sampling method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Tamaño: 512x768 o 768x512

  • Hires fix: 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G (Denoising strenght: 0.35, Upscale by: 2)

  1. English:

I have used a new configuration so that the result is much more realistic. Try using EpicRealism.

It is possible that the name of the LORA will change, so do not copy it directly from CIVITAI, rather select it from the LORAS section of Stable Diffusion so that there are no errors in the generation of images.

My setup using EpicRealism:

  • Lora Strength: 1

  • Prompt: simple explanation of the image (try first without extra keywords)

    In the case of this LORA, the prompt must begin with "A woman...".

  • Negative prompt: cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2), asian, chinese, (epiCNegative:0.9)

  • Sampling steps: >20 (if image has errors or artefacts use higher Steps)

  • CFG Scale: 5

  • Sampling method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Size: 512x768 or 768x512

  • Hires fix: 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G (Denoising strength: 0.35, Upscale by: 2)

V1.0

Lora Strength: 0.8

This LORA has been trained with the Photon model.

Follow the indications of the model to have a good result:

  • Prompt: A simple sentence in natural language describing the image.

    In the case of this Lora, the prompt must begin with "a woman...". Better separately: "A woman, (the rest of the indications),...

  • Negative: "cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2)"

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras | Steps: 25 | CFG Scale: 6

  • Clip Skip 2

  • Size: 512x768 or 768x512

  • Hires.fix: 4x-UltraSharp | steps: 10 | Denoising: 0.45 | Upscale x 2

(avoid using negative embeddings unless absolutely necessary)

items.description:
NOTE: ALL CHARACTERS IN THE IMAGES ARE ADULTS.

How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both penance_arknights.pt and penance_arknights.safetensors, then use penance_arknights.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use penance_arknights.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

それらを同時に使用してください。この場合、penance_arknights.ptとpenance_arknights.safetensorsの両方をダウンロード する必要があります。penance_arknights.ptをテクスチャ反転埋め込みとして使用し、同時にpenance_arknights.safetensorsをLoRAとして使用してください。

同时使用它们。在这种情况下，您需要下载penance_arknights.pt和penance_arknights.safetensors这两个文件，然后将penance_arknights.pt用作纹理反转嵌入， 同时使用penance_arknights.safetensors作为LoRA。

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is penance_arknights, and the recommended tags are masterpiece, best quality, highres, solo, {penance_arknights:1.10}, animal_ears, wolf_ears, extra_ears, long_hair, wolf_girl, brown_hair, yellow_eyes, breasts, ascot, white_ascot, tail, wolf_tail, bangs, hair_between_eyes, jewelry, large_breasts, very_long_hair.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Penance Arknights

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is fine-tune the tags you use.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/penance_arknights, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/penance_arknights, which may be help to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

items.name: MoltenArt V1 (SD 1.5)
items.description:
Yet another SD 1.5 Checkpoint merge…

This is a Checkpoint merge model that I’ve been working on for a little while with the goal of achieving a different (even slightly) look to the results, especially in the face, from other models out there so far. I’ve tested this model against other popular models, and I prefer the results of this model most of the time.

I am sharing it in case there are other people that like its results also.

This is a realistic model that can handle fantasy, Loras, lycoris, textual inversions, Booru tags, simple or complex prompts, etc.

Basic Negative Prompt: "ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, (badhandv4:1.2), (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale))"

Settings used for the examples:

VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned ( https://civitai.com/models/76118/vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned )

base resolution: 512 x 768

Euler A or DPM++ SDE Karras

Sampling Steps: 23-28; 

CFG Scale 7-8

Hires.fix with 20 Hires Steps using 4x-UltraSharp_Balanced upscaler

Upscale by 2.0

Denoising strength 0.4 – 0.5

Clip Skip 2

ENSD “31337”

After Detailer ( https://github.com/Bing-su/adetailer) can improve faces in the distance

Brightness Adjustment_B_1.1|밝기 조정|明度調整 Lora ( https://civitai.com/models/95601 )to lighten images that are too dark.

items.name: RIM 理芽 SDXL
items.description:
RIM from Kamitsubaki studio

Main trigger word is rim

I still don't know optimal settings for SDXL, but following settings produce pretty good results.

  • Positive Prompts: anime,(masterpiece, top quality, best quality, official art, beautiful and aesthetic:1.2), cinematic lighting, upper body, extreme detailed, studio anime, key visual, (bioluminescent details:1.1), (subsurface scattering:1.1), colorful, rim, virtual youtuber, 1girl, solo, blue hair, multicolored hair, red hair, short hair, bangs, multicolored eyes, hood, <lora:rim_sdxl_v1:1.0> looking at viewer, dynamic pose, dynamic angle, dynamic lighting

  • Negative Prompts: (worst quality:1.2, low quality:1.2, bad anatomy:1.2, cropped hands, extra digit, fewer digit), text, error, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, artist name, unaestheticXLv1

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Step: 30

  • CFG Scale: 8~10

Tags - This csv file contains all of the prompts that were used when I trained this model

I am not the artist of the character nor RIM herself nor related to thinkr incoporation.

All right reserved to RIM and KAMITSUBAKI Studio(THINKR inc)

Maintaining a stable diffusion model is very resource-burning. Please consider to support me via Ko-fi.

===

This is a LyCORIS model of Torino Aqua-sensei's style trained on AingDiffusion v8.0 with 233 images and a total of 2330 steps.

Use between 0.6~0.8 strength. In some cases you might wanna lower it more.

This model is released for educational purposes only and not for commercial use.

If asked to be taken down by Torino-sensei, I will happily take this down.

===

This is the first LoCon I trained. I still need to learn a lot of things. I hope you understand.

items.name: Jessica Hamby from True Blood TV Show (LoRA SDXL 1.0)
items.description:
This LoRA has been trained after carefully selecting 91 images, most of them from True Blood TV show captions. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them.

When downloading model and testing it, try to copy any of the prompts I have used, and make some variations in order to get other images you prefer. Have fun!

There is a great range of improvement in base model, especially regarding weird limbs or hands (yes, it's still there!! :( ) Anyway I'm satisfied with this model, waiting for future improved photorealistic checkpoints based on SDXL base 1.0.

LoRA weights should be between 0.8 and 1.3 in my experience (but you're free to test)

For portraits you can use 896 x 1152, 768 x 1344, 832 x 1216, 640 x 1536 or even 768x1024 resolutions.

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

Jessica Hamby is a fictional character in the True Blood series, portrayed by Deborah Ann Woll. In the series, which chronicles the life of human waitress Sookie Stackhouse and her friends after vampires make themselves known to humans, Jessica is a newly turned vampire who must learn to deal with her vampiric abilities, weaknesses, and altered lifestyle.

Notice: This free work is intended for art and illustration purposes of emergent technology and not intended nor' trained for making illicit images, as the author I've taken care to not use any private data in the training process or designed it for such purposes. By downloading this model you are agreeing with the aforementioned intent and that you will not use my work to create / share images of a potentially immoral and / or illegal nature.
